CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 28, 1956, pg. A19, reads: "SPECIAL GUESTS...at the GLC CLub luncheon at Clark Memorial Baptist Church, Homestead, last Friday, were the above quintet which sat at the guest table with Mrs. Alex Murray and her family. Mrs. Murray was honored by the club.  Seated, left to right, Mmes. Kay Douglass and Sylvia Hairston of Cleveland, Ohio.  Standing in same order, Mrs. Gladys Mason, Chicago, Ill.; Mrs. Ella Ashby, Pittsburgh, and Miss Eunice McGuster, Chicago.  Miss Guster is the daughter of Mrs. Mason. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five women of GLC Club, seated left to right: Kay Douglass and Sylvia Hairston; standing: Gladys Mason, Ella Ashby, and Eunice McGuster, posed in Clark Memorial Baptist Church, Homestead
